				<h1><span class="small">Call For</span><span class="large">Artists</span></h1>
				<p>
					Ben Hecht had a dream where hard journalism and fiction joined to record the stories of everyone: the scoundrel, the criminal, the hero, the bum, the guilty, the innocent, the worker, the dreamer, the hopeless, the believer, and even the artist. In writing <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=O0MLAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA285&lpg=PA285&dq=grass+figures+by+ben+hecht&source=bl&ots=5tNwXp12KN&sig=r0L_x5nUOyg0s7Cpg2FkpnHWFX8&hl=en&sa=X&ei=zAmuUp7wC8jyqQHPmIDYAw&ved=0CFIQ6AEwBQ#v=onepage&q=grass%20figures%20by%20ben%20hecht&f=false" target="_BLANK"><i>1001 Afternoons in Chicago</i></a>, Hecht sought to capture the authentic city by incorporating all Chicagoâ€™s faces and personalities.
				</p>
				<p>
					Half King Productions wishes to do the same and seeks the works and visions of Chicago's digital artists, animators, and illustrators to help translate Ben Hecht's stories into a new reality: <i>1001 Afternoons in Chicago: The Film</i>. 
				</p>
				<p>
					By viewing the clips below, you will see a rough cut edit of sequences from the film. The clips do not have any color correction, grading, or audio work; the final film will look and sound significantly different and better. 
				</p>
				<p>
					A red box indicates the sequence where we would like to see animation. Each clip has been given a general direction of tone or mood to follow as a guideline. The art and vision is still completely up to you!
					<!-- So, if you feel inspired by Hecht's writing or the sequence itself, feel free to dream, play, and create any kind of animation! --> 
				</p>
				<p>
					After you've created a sequence and uploaded your sequence to YouTube with the heading of the clip (ex. Call for Artists: Sequence 1), our production team will see if we can incorporate your sequence into the final film. 
				</p>
				<p>
				<h1 style="margin-top:60px;"><span class="small seq">Sequence 1</span></h1>
				<p class="call-lead">
					General Tone: the endlessly shifting and replicating faces of the city, seeing yourself everywhere and nowhere, exciting but disconcerting at the same time.
				</p>
				<div class="videoWrapper">
					<iframe src="//player.vimeo.com/video/82968560" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe>
				</div>
				
					
				
				<hr>
				</p>
				<p>
				<h1 style="margin-top:60px;"><span class="small seq">Sequence 2</span></h1>
				<p class="call-lead">
					General Tone: the distortion of the Carnival mirror, funny, beautiful and frightening.
				</p>
				<div class="videoWrapper">
					<iframe src="//player.vimeo.com/video/82968561" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe>
				</div>
				
					
				
				<hr>
				</p>
				<p>
				<h1 style="margin-top:60px;"><span class="small seq">Sequence 3</span></h1>
				<p class="call-lead">
					General Tone: wild energy and eccentricity. Sklarz is a man soaring on the heights of joy before jumping off the cliff. 
				</p>
				<div class="videoWrapper">
					<iframe src="//player.vimeo.com/video/82973753" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe>
				</div>
				
					
				
				<hr>
				</p>
